HEADWORD: Robinet
<hw>Rob"i*net</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The chaffinch; -- called also
<altname>roberd</altname>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The European
robin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A military engine formerly used for throwing darts
and stones.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Robing</ent>⟦br⟧
